thermal: broadcom: ns-thermal: expose the zone as a hwmon device

DT thermal zones are registered with tzp->no_hwmon = true (see
thermal_of.c), so the thermal core does not create a hwmon device for
them automatically. SoC sensor drivers that want a hwmon interface must
opt back in via devm_thermal_add_hwmon_sysfs(), as the MediaTek
(auxadc/lvts) and amlogic drivers do.

Without this the Northstar PVT sensor is only reachable through
/sys/class/thermal/thermal_zoneN/temp and never appears under
/sys/class/hwmon, so lm-sensors ("sensors") reports nothing. Register
the hwmon device so the zone shows up as cpu_thermal-virtual-0, matching
the other ARM targets and letting userspace read the CPU temperature via
the standard hwmon path.
--- a/drivers/thermal/broadcom/ns-thermal.c
+++ b/drivers/thermal/broadcom/ns-thermal.c
@@ -8,6 +8,8 @@
 #include <linux/platform_device.h>
 #include <linux/thermal.h>
 
+#include "../thermal_hwmon.h"
+
 #define PVTMON_CONTROL0					0x00
 #define PVTMON_CONTROL0_SEL_MASK			0x0000000e
 #define PVTMON_CONTROL0_SEL_TEMP_MONITOR		0x00000000
@@ -60,6 +62,8 @@
 		return PTR_ERR(tz);
 	}
 
+	devm_thermal_add_hwmon_sysfs(dev, tz);
+
 	platform_set_drvdata(pdev, pvtmon);
 
 	return 0;
